# Aerodynamic Wing Optimization â€“ GT3 Rear Wing Configuration

This project uses nonlinear optimization to identify the ideal rear-wing fore-aft position (x) and height (z) for a GT3 car at Road America. The objective is to minimize lap time while satisfying straight-line cooling/load constraints.

## ğŸ Scenario
As the GT3 engineering intern, you must deliver an optimal wing configuration before qualifying. The model uses nonlinear relationships between:
- Lift coefficient (CL)
- Drag coefficient (CD)
- Downforce saturation benefit
- Drag penalty
- Straight-line cooling load constraint

(Source: *Project 2.4 PDF* MSPE 29800, Purdue University) :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

